    },
    {
      "text": "Daryl responds, \"",
      "start": 169.516,
      "end": 170.476,
      "words": [
        "Daryl",
        "responds"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Indeed,",
      "start": 170.716,
      "end": 171.356,
      "words": [
        "Indeed"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "it does.\"",
      "start": 171.356,
      "end": 171.836,
      "words": [
        "it",
        "does"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "This is a common conversational way to say yes or agree with someone.",
      "start": 172.316,
      "end": 176.556,
      "words": [
        "This",
        "is",
        "a",
        "common",
        "conversational",
        "way",
        "to",
        "say",
        "yes",
        "or",
        "agree",
        "with",
        "someone"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "We say\" indeed\" followed by\" do\" in the present tense.",
      "start": 176.876,
      "end": 180.236,
      "words": [
        "We",
        "say",
        "indeed",
        "followed",
        "by",
        "do",
        "in",
        "the",
        "present",
        "tense"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "On Christmas morning,",
      "start": 181.1,
      "end": 182.3,
      "words": [
        "On",
        "Christmas",
        "morning"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Daryl asks his children to queue up on the stairs so he can check for Santa Claus,",
      "start": 182.46,
      "end": 188.3,
      "words": [
        "Daryl",
        "asks",
        "his",
        "children",
        "to",
        "queue",
        "up",
        "on",
        "the",
        "stairs",
        "so",
        "he",
        "can",
        "check",
        "for",
        "Santa",
        "Claus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "just like Daryl's father did when he was small.",
      "start": 188.7,
      "end": 191.26,
      "words": [
        "just",
        "like",
        "Daryl's",
        "father",
        "did",
        "when",
        "he",
        "was",
        "small"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And Claudia likes this tradition,",
      "start": 191.66,
      "end": 193.58,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "Claudia",
        "likes",
        "this",
        "tradition"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "imagining the children waiting on the stairs dying for their presents.",
      "start": 193.82,
      "end": 198.06,
      "words": [
        "imagining",
        "the",
        "children",
        "waiting",
        "on",
        "the",
        "stairs",
        "dying",
        "for",
        "their",
        "presents"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "We use the phrase\" dying for\" informally when someone really wants something.",
      "start": 198.46,
      "end": 203.18,
      "words": [
        "We",
        "use",
        "the",
        "phrase",
        "dying",
        "for",
        "informally",
        "when",
        "someone",
        "really",
        "wants",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Now.",
      "start": 203.5,
      "end": 203.9,
      "words": [
        "Now"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Now,",
      "start": 203.532,
      "end": 203.932,
      "words": [
        "Now"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "when we remember Christmas from the past and feel nostalgia,",
      "start": 203.932,
      "end": 207.212,
      "words": [
        "when",
        "we",
        "remember",
        "Christmas",
        "from",
        "the",
        "past",
        "and",
        "feel",
        "nostalgia"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "we often remember things in a very positive way.",
      "start": 207.532,
      "end": 210.572,
      "words": [
        "we",
        "often",
        "remember",
        "things",
        "in",
        "a",
        "very",
        "positive",
        "way"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "But was the past definitely better?",
      "start": 211.132,
      "end": 213.292,
      "words": [
        "But",
        "was",
        "the",
        "past",
        "definitely",
        "better"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Are we remembering correctly?",
      "start": 213.772,
      "end": 215.452,
      "words": [
        "Are",
        "we",
        "remembering",
        "correctly"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "This is what Claudia Hammond asked Katherine Love Day,",
      "start": 215.932,
      "end": 219.132,
      "words": [
        "This",
        "is",
        "what",
        "Claudia",
        "Hammond",
        "asked",
        "Katherine",
        "Love",
        "Day"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "who's a professor of cognitive neuroscience,",
      "start": 219.372,
      "end": 222.252,
      "words": [
        "who's",
        "a",
        "professor",
        "of",
        "cognitive",
        "neuroscience"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "on BBC Radio Four programme All in the Mind.",
      "start": 222.572,
      "end": 225.532,
      "words": [
        "on",
        "BBC",
        "Radio",
        "Four",
        "programme",
        "All",
        "in",
        "the",
        "Mind"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "How accurate are nostalgic memories?",
      "start": 225.772,
      "end": 228.012,
      "words": [
        "How",
        "accurate",
        "are",
        "nostalgic",
        "memories"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Are they accurate?",
      "start": 228.012,
      "end": 228.572,
      "words": [
        "Are",
        "they",
        "accurate"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Well,",
      "start": 228.972,
      "end": 229.292,
      "words": [
        "Well"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "they're often going to be rose tinted and made more positive,",
      "start": 229.292,
      "end": 232.812,
      "words": [
        "they're",
        "often",
        "going",
        "to",
        "be",
        "rose",
        "tinted",
        "and",
        "made",
        "more",
        "positive"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "of course,",
      "start": 232.812,
      "end": 233.372,
      "words": [
        "of",
        "course"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "and that's what we do with our past generally,",
      "start": 233.372,
      "end": 235.372,
      "words": [
        "and",
        "that's",
        "what",
        "we",
        "do",
        "with",
        "our",
        "past",
        "generally"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "but it doesn't really matter.",
      "start": 235.532,
      "end": 236.972,
      "words": [
        "but",
        "it",
        "doesn't",
        "really",
        "matter"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "I mean,",
      "start": 236.972,
      "end": 237.372,
      "words": [
        "I",
        "mean"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "in our work we've just shown that the function of memory is not about accuracy.",
      "start": 237.772,
      "end": 242.412,
      "words": [
        "in",
        "our",
        "work",
        "we've",
        "just",
        "shown",
        "that",
        "the",
        "function",
        "of",
        "memory",
        "is",
        "not",
        "about",
        "accuracy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "It doesn't matter if some of the details are wrong,",
      "start": 242.412,
      "end": 244.572,
      "words": [
        "It",
        "doesn't",
        "matter",
        "if",
        "some",
        "of",
        "the",
        "details",
        "are",
        "wrong"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "it doesn't matter how we frame it.",
      "start": 244.572,
      "end": 246.092,
      "words": [
        "it",
        "doesn't",
        "matter",
        "how",
        "we",
        "frame",
        "it"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "In fact,",
      "start": 246.172,
      "end": 246.572,
      "words": [
        "In",
        "fact"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "it's actually better for us in a way to reframe our memories and to slightly adjust them to suit who we are now.",
      "start": 246.572,
      "end": 252.092,
      "words": [
        "it's",
        "actually",
        "better",
        "for",
        "us",
        "in",
        "a",
        "way",
        "to",
        "reframe",
        "our",
        "memories",
        "and",
        "to",
        "slightly",
        "adjust",
        "them",
        "to",
        "suit",
        "who",
        "we",
        "are",
        "now"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Katherine says that our memories are often rose tinted.",
      "start": 252.252,
      "end": 255.372,
      "words": [
        "Katherine",
        "says",
        "that",
        "our",
        "memories",
        "are",
        "often",
        "rose",
        "tinted"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "If a memory is rose tinted,",
      "start": 255.692,
      "end": 257.292,
      "words": [
        "If",
        "a",
        "memory",
        "is",
        "rose",
        "tinted"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "we only see the positive things about it and don't remember any of the bad parts.",
      "start": 257.452,
      "end": 262.012,
      "words": [
        "we",
        "only",
        "see",
        "the",
        "positive",
        "things",
        "about",
        "it",
        "and",
        "don't",
        "remember",
        "any",
        "of",
        "the",
        "bad",
        "parts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "But according.",
      "start": 262.252,
      "end": 263.052,
      "words": [
        "But",
        "according"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "To Catherine,",
      "start": 263.052,
      "end": 263.852,
      "words": [
        "To",
        "Catherine"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "it doesn't always matter.",
      "start": 263.852,
      "end": 265.532,
      "words": [
        "it",
        "doesn't",
        "always",
        "matter"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "She says the function of memory is not accuracy.",
      "start": 265.852,
      "end": 269.372,
      "words": [
        "She",
        "says",
        "the",
        "function",
        "of",
        "memory",
        "is",
        "not",
        "accuracy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Function means the purpose of something.",
      "start": 269.692,
      "end": 271.932,
      "words": [
        "Function",
        "means",
        "the",
        "purpose",
        "of",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "In fact,",
      "start": 272.012,
      "end": 272.572,
      "words": [
        "In",
        "fact"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Catherine says that how we frame a memory doesn't matter.",
      "start": 272.812,
      "end": 276.012,
      "words": [
        "Catherine",
        "says",
        "that",
        "how",
        "we",
        "frame",
        "a",
        "memory",
        "doesn't",
        "matter"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Frame can be used as a verb to mean how we think of or describe something,",
      "start": 276.412,
      "end": 280.812,
      "words": [
        "Frame",
        "can",
        "be",
        "used",
        "as",
        "a",
        "verb",
        "to",
        "mean",
        "how",
        "we",
        "think",
        "of",
        "or",
        "describe",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "like a memory.",
      "start": 281.052,
      "end": 281.852,
      "words": [
        "like",
        "a",
        "memory"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "So our memories aren't that accurate,",
      "start": 282.38,
      "end": 285.1,
      "words": [
        "So",
        "our",
        "memories",
        "aren't",
        "that",
        "accurate"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "and it isn't that important unless,",
      "start": 285.42,
      "end": 287.42,
      "words": [
        "and",
        "it",
        "isn't",
        "that",
        "important",
        "unless"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "of course,",
      "start": 287.42,
      "end": 287.98,
      "words": [
        "of",
        "course"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "we need to remember factual details about something important.",
      "start": 287.98,
      "end": 291.5,
      "words": [
        "we",
        "need",
        "to",
        "remember",
        "factual",
        "details",
        "about",
        "something",
        "important"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "So our nostalgia about Christmas memories might not be based on what things were actually like in the past,",
      "start": 291.74,
      "end": 298.38,
      "words": [
        "So",
        "our",
        "nostalgia",
        "about",
        "Christmas",
        "memories",
        "might",
        "not",
        "be",
        "based",
        "on",
        "what",
        "things",
        "were",
        "actually",
        "like",
        "in",
        "the",
        "past"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "but we shouldn't worry too much.",
      "start": 298.7,
      "end": 299.98,
      "words": [
        "but",
        "we",
        "shouldn't",
        "worry",
        "too",
        "much"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And I think it's time I revealed the answer to my quiz question,",
      "start": 300.46,
      "end": 303.9,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "I",
        "think",
        "it's",
        "time",
        "I",
        "revealed",
        "the",
        "answer",
        "to",
        "my",
        "quiz",
        "question"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Beth.",
      "start": 303.9,
      "end": 304.22,
      "words": [
        "Beth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "I asked what has become a traditional food to eat in Japan at Christmas time.",
      "start": 304.62,
      "end": 310.14,
      "words": [
        "I",
        "asked",
        "what",
        "has",
        "become",
        "a",
        "traditional",
        "food",
        "to",
        "eat",
        "in",
        "Japan",
        "at",
        "Christmas",
        "time"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And I said fried chicken.",
      "start": 310.38,
      "end": 312.3,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "I",
        "said",
        "fried",
        "chicken"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Was I right?",
      "start": 312.3,
      "end": 312.7,
      "words": [
        "Was",
        "I",
        "right"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "You were absolutely correct.",
      "start": 313.1,
      "end": 314.62,
      "words": [
        "You",
        "were",
        "absolutely",
        "correct"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Let's recap the vocabulary we've learnt,",
      "start": 314.86,
      "end": 317.02,
      "words": [
        "Let's",
        "recap",
        "the",
        "vocabulary",
        "we've",
        "learnt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "starting with nostalgia a feeling of happiness and also some sadness when you think about a thing that happened in the past.",
      "start": 317.18,
      "end": 324.78,
      "words": [
        "starting",
        "with",
        "nostalgia",
        "a",
        "feeling",
        "of",
        "happiness",
        "and",
        "also",
        "some",
        "sadness",
        "when",
        "you",
        "think",
        "about",
        "a",
        "thing",
        "that",
        "happened",
        "in",
        "the",
        "past"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "The phrase 'indeed' followed by the present simple form of 'do' can be used informally instead of answering 'yes'.",
      "start": 325.02,
      "end": 332.22,
      "words": [
        "The",
        "phrase",
        "'indeed'",
        "followed",
        "by",
        "the",
        "present",
        "simple",
        "form",
        "of",
        "'do'",
        "can",
        "be",
        "used",
        "informally",
        "instead",
        "of",
        "answering",
        "'yes'"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "For example,",
      "start": 332.54,
      "end": 333.26,
      "words": [
        "For",
        "example"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Beth,",
      "start": 333.26,
      "end": 333.58,
      "words": [
        "Beth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "do you enjoy eating Brussels sprouts at Christmas?",
      "start": 333.82,
      "end": 336.14,
      "words": [
        "do",
        "you",
        "enjoy",
        "eating",
        "Brussels",
        "sprouts",
        "at",
        "Christmas"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Indeed I do.",
      "start": 336.3,
      "end": 337.42,
      "words": [
        "Indeed",
        "I",
        "do"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Dying for something is an informal phrasal verb we use to say that we really want something.",
      "start": 338.124,
      "end": 343.564,
      "words": [
        "Dying",
        "for",
        "something",
        "is",
        "an",
        "informal",
        "phrasal",
        "verb",
        "we",
        "use",
        "to",
        "say",
        "that",
        "we",
        "really",
        "want",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Rose tinted means seeing only the positive parts of something and not the bad parts.",
      "start": 343.724,
      "end": 348.604,
      "words": [
        "Rose",
        "tinted",
        "means",
        "seeing",
        "only",
        "the",
        "positive",
        "parts",
        "of",
        "something",
        "and",
        "not",
        "the",
        "bad",
        "parts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Function means the purpose of something.",
      "start": 348.844,
      "end": 350.924,
      "words": [
        "Function",
        "means",
        "the",
        "purpose",
        "of",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "And frame can be used as a verb to mean how we think of or describe something.",
      "start": 351.404,
      "end": 356.204,
      "words": [
        "And",
        "frame",
        "can",
        "be",
        "used",
        "as",
        "a",
        "verb",
        "to",
        "mean",
        "how",
        "we",
        "think",
        "of",
        "or",
        "describe",
        "something"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Once again,",
      "start": 356.748,
      "end": 357.388,
      "words": [
        "Once",
        "again"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "our six minutes are up.",
      "start": 357.548,
      "end": 358.828,
      "words": [
        "our",
        "six",
        "minutes",
        "are",
        "up"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Once.",
      "start": 356.764,
      "end": 356.924,
      "words": [
        "Once"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Test what you've learned in the episode with the quiz and worksheets on our website.",
      "start": 359.228,
      "end": 363.708,
      "words": [
        "Test",
        "what",
        "you've",
        "learned",
        "in",
        "the",
        "episode",
        "with",
        "the",
        "quiz",
        "and",
        "worksheets",
        "on",
        "our",
        "website"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "To all our listeners who are celebrating Christmas,",
      "start": 364.028,
      "end": 366.348,
      "words": [
        "To",
        "all",
        "our",
        "listeners",
        "who",
        "are",
        "celebrating",
        "Christmas"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "merry Christmas and we hope you all have a good end to the year.",
      "start": 366.748,
      "end": 370.268,
      "words": [
        "merry",
        "Christmas",
        "and",
        "we",
        "hope",
        "you",
        "all",
        "have",
        "a",
        "good",
        "end",
        "to",
        "the",
        "year"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "See you soon.",
      "start": 370.348,
      "end": 370.988,
      "words": [
        "See",
        "you",
        "soon"
      ]
